{
  "text": "Consider states (on A) of the form [CITATION_1] where \u03c9 p is a state of the particle system and \u03c9 (\u03b2) ri is the (\u03b1 t ri , \u03b2 i )-KMS state of the i-th reservoir. The set of states which are normal w.r.t. \u03c9 0 is the same for any choice of \u03c9 p . A state normal w.r.t. \u03c9 0 will be called a \u03b2 1 \u03b2 2 -normal state.",
